reviews.reviewbody:
Ravindra & Tiraj great effort, thanks guys for the download, music is for my father in-law.
I guess the music speaks for itself.
good bless these guys. Finally listen to a good music from ceylon

Edit: Wow thanks..thanks...thanks!
Cannot tell how much I appreciate this. Was looking for this song for a long long time.
Have great day.
And already downloading the others!
Cheers 
....

Thanks a lot Tiraj.
Just an aditional request. I'm looking for an oldie.
As far as I can remember, it was a 'viridu'.
It was about two villagers (husband & wife) visiting the city in a poya day and they mistake a hotel to be a 'Dansala' and in the end have to pay for what they ate. While going back wife scolds the husband saying something like 'Poya dawase mas kewata thota pala dunna' or to that effect. If you can find this one pls upload.

Thank you very much for your review. The song you have requested is already in this playlist. It's called 21. Bohoma aatha Gammaneka.

Also check out,  Old Sinhalese Folk Music from Ceylon playlist if you have an interest in this line of work.

Enjoy
Tiraj
I am traveling in Sri Lanka and tried to find CD from here, but having a hard time.   This is tremendous addition to my trip.
reviews.reviewtitle: Wonderful music from old Sri Lanka (Ceylon)

reviews.reviewbody: This is a very good collection and thanks a lot for sharing it
